YELLOW FEVER - BRAZIL (PARA)
****************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Yellow fever - French Guiana 980527224014
Date: Thu, 28 May 1998 01:08:07 -0400 (EDT)
From: Jack Woodall <woodall@wadsworth.org>
Source: newspaper O Povo (Fortaleza, CE)
<http://www.agestado.com/links/index.htm>
Via: promed-port@usa.healthnet.org [Summarized from the Portuguese by Mod.JW

>From February to May 1998 there have been 14 cases of yellow fever,
including 3 deaths, 70% of them in the municipality of Afua, in the Marajo
archipelago at the mouth of the Amazon, in Para state. In that
municipality, 80% of the population is being vaccinated. All the cases
were confirmed by the Evandro Chagas Institute in Belem [a WHO
Collaborating Centre & national reference center for arboviruses.
Belem is a large city at the mouth of the Amazon, and the capital of Para
state. Precautionary YF vaccination will begin there on 29 May. It will
also be done in 58 of the 142 municipalities in the state.
--
